1317]]\n<ref>[[2016\u201317 EFL League Two]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=February 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Wigan Athletic F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naismith, Kal}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Cowdenbeath F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Partick Thistle F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Accrington Stanley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Portsmouth F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Kal Naismith\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Kal Alexander Naismith<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/image/201920/general-news/efl-squad-numbering-06.09.2019.pdf |title=Notification of shirt numbers: Wigan Athletic |publisher=English Football League |page=76 |accessdate=28 October 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|2|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Glasgow]], Scotland\n| height = {{convert|1.86|m|order=flip}}<ref name=\"11v11\"/>\n| position = [[Utility player#Association football|Utility player]]\n| currentclub = [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]\n| clubnumber = 33\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]\n| years1 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs1 = [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]                              | caps1 = 17 | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2011      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]] (loan)             | caps2 = 9  | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2012      | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]] (loan)     | caps3 = 8  | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2013\u20132015 | clubs4 = [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]        | caps4 = 73 | goals4 = 14\n| years5 = 2015\u20132018 | clubs5 = [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]]                        | caps5 = 81 | goals5 = 18\n| years6 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan) | caps6 = 4  | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2018\u2013     | clubs7 = [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]                | caps7 = 57  | goals7 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2007\u20132008\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national under-16 football team|Scotland U16]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2008\u20132009\n| nationalteam2 = [[Scotland national under-17 football team|Scotland U17]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 8\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| club-update = 15:30, 28 February 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 31 January 2012\n}}\n'''Kal Alexander Naismith''' (born 18 February 1992) is a Scottish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]].\n\nA [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] youth graduate, Naismith made his breakthrough into the first team in the 2012\u201313 season, after loan spells at [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]] and [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]]. He has represented Scotland at [[Scotland national under-16 football team|under-16]] and [[Scotland national under-17 football team|under-17]] level. He plays either as an out and out striker, as a winger or in an attacking midfield position. His main attributes are his ball control and skill.\n\n==Club career==\n===Rangers===\nNaismith was sent on loan to Cowdenbeath and Partick Thistle during the 2011\u201312 season. On his return from loan Naismith made his debut as a substitute on 29 July 2012, in a 2\u20131 win over [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]] in the [[Scottish Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19032245 | title=Brechin City 1\u20132 Rangers | publisher=BBC Sport | date=29 July 2012 | accessdate=30 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe scored his first goal for Rangers against Forres Mechanics in the Second Round of the 2012 Scottish Cup. On 9 August 2013 he mutually agreed with Rangers to terminate his contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rangers.co.uk/news/headlines/item/4753-weve-done-our-homework|title=We've Done Our Homework - Rangers Football Club, Official Website|date=9 August 2013|access-date=10 August 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813022853/http://www.rangers.co.uk/news/headlines/item/4753-weve-done-our-homework#|archive-date=13 August 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n====Cowdenbeath (loan)====\nNaismith joined [[Scottish Second Division]] club Cowdenbeath on loan at the end of August 2011. He made his debut on 10 September against [[East Fife F.C.|East Fife]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14868107.stm | title=Cowdenbeath 3\u20132 East Fife | publisher=BBC Sport | date=10 September 2011 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> going on to score his first goals for the club on 24 September scoring both goals in their 2\u20131 win over [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/15027701.stm | title=Cowdenbeath 2\u20131 Albion Rovers | publisher=BBC Sport | date=24 September 2011 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> With matches limited due to call offs<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/16223673.stm | title=Scottish football fixture card hit by cold snap | publisher=BBC Sport | date=17 December 2011 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> his last game came on 10 December against [[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/16122478.stm | title=Cowdenbeath 0\u20130 Arbroath | publisher=BBC Sport | date=10 December 2011 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n====Partick Thistle (loan)====\nOn 5 January 2012 Naismith joined [[Scottish First Division]] club Partick Thistle on loan until the end of the season,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ptfc.co.uk/news/2011-2012/january_2012/further_loan_signing_to_join_thistle | title=Further Loan | publisher=[[Partick Thistle F.C.]] | date=5 January 2012 | accessdate=8 January 2012 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130406132212/http://ptfc.co.uk/news/2011-2012/january_2012/further_loan_signing_to_join_thistle | archivedate=6 April 2013 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> however was unable to play against [[Queen of the South F.C.|Queen of the South]] in the [[Scottish Cup]] that weekend as he was cup tied<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.theglaswegian.co.uk/glasgow-sport/2012/01/05/partick-thistle-complete-loan-deal-for-rangers-winger-kal-naismith-102692-23681792/ | title=Partick Thistle Complete Loan Deal For Rangers Winger Kal Naismith | publisher=The Glaswegian | date=5 January 2012 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> having played for Cowdenbeath earlier in the season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/15704728.stm | title=Boness Utd 0\u20133 Cowdenbeath | publisher=BBC Sport | date=19 November 2011 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> He made his debut on 13 January playing from the start in their 1\u20130 defeat to [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/16558299.stm | title=Hamilton Accies 1\u20130 Partick Thistle | publisher=BBC Sport | date=13 January 2012 | accessdate=15 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Accrington Stanley===\nIn the 2013 summer, Naismith was given a trial at [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]], completing a switch to them on a free transfer shortly after.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/accrington-stanley/transfer-talk/news/naismith-seals-accrington-switch_97787.html|title=Kal Naismith seals Accrington Stanley switch|publisher=Sports Mole|date=10 August 2013|accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 10 August, starting in a 2\u20132 home draw against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]].\n\nNaismith scored his first goal for Stanley on 22 October 2013, netting the winner in a 2\u20131 home success over [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]]. He also scored braces against [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]] and [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]], finishing the season with ten goals in 38 appearances.\n\nNaismith was also an undisputed starter for the club in 2014\u201315, scoring four goals in 35 games.\n\n===Portsmouth===\nOn 28 May 2015, Naismith signed a three-year deal with fellow [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.portsmouthfc.co.uk/news/article/pompey-sign-winger-kal-naismith-from-accrington-stanley-2474444.aspx?|title=Naismith pens Pompey deal|publisher=Portsmouth FC|date=28 May 2015|accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nNaismith scored 13 goals in the season which saw Portsmouth finish as champions of League 2, clinched on the last day of the season.\n\nAt the end of the 2017\u201318 season, Portsmouth announced that he rejected a new deal from the club, deciding to pursue other options elsewhere.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portsmouthfc.co.uk/news/2018/may/four-players-set-to-leave-pompey/|title=Four Players Set To Leave Pompey|publisher=Portsmouth FC|date=9 May 2018|access-date=9 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44061274|title=Kai Naismith exits Portsmouth, who release trio of Jez Bedford, Nicke Kabamba and Theo Widdrington|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=9 May 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n===Wigan Athletic===\nOn 30 May 2018, Naismith signed a three-year deal with the side [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]. He scored his first goal for Wigan in a 4-2 loss at [[Sheffield United]] on 27 October 2018.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45923355\n|title=Sheffield United 4-2 Wigan\n|publisher=BBC\n|date=27 October 2018 |accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nNaismith has represented Scotland at under-16 level<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfa.net/football_player_profile.cfm?page=1921&playerID=41755&squadID=17 | title=Kai Naismith SFA | publisher=Scottish Football Association | accessdate=8 January 2012 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> making his debut against Wales on 5 October 2007.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/international_fixture_details.cfm?page=108&matchID=71656 | title=WALES v SCOTLAND | publisher=SFA | date=5 October 2007 | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> His first goal came on 29 November against England.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfa.net/international_fixture_details.cfm?page=1921&matchID=72499 | title=Scotland v England | publisher=SFA | date=29 November 2007 | accessdate=8 January 2012 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He later represented the under-17 team making eight appearances.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfa.net/football_player_profile.cfm?page=1921&playerID=41755&squadID=13 | title=Kai Naismith SFA under 17 | publisher=Scottish Football Association | accessdate=8 January 2012 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|5 May 2018}}<ref>{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/kal-naismith/197552/ | title=Kal Naismith | publisher=Soccerway | accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" style=\"vertical-align:center;\"|[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]\n|[[2011-12 Scotti